By contrast, when the transmit antennas are distributed and randomly placed, most of the terms $(\cos\gamma_{us}-\cos\gamma_{ut})^2$ in (\ref{pCellRadius}) are not negligible, thereby the volumes of coherent signal have smaller dimensions in all directions.
For example,  {Fig.\ \ref{{fig:Distributed}}} shows the envelope of the SINR for the same conditions as in {Fig.\ \ref{{fig:CentralizedULA}}} but for distributed transmit antennas instead.
